------------------------------------------------------
SLI (Service Level Indicator)
------------------------------------------------------
Definition: A metric that measures the actual performance of a service.
Example: 99.95% uptime in the last 30 days.
------------------------------------------------------




------------------------------------------------------
SLO (Service Level Objective)
------------------------------------------------------
Definition: A target value for an SLI, setting an expected level of service.
Example: 99.9% uptime target.
------------------------------------------------------





------------------------------------------------------
SLA (Service Level Agreement)
------------------------------------------------------
Definition: A legal agreement with penalties if service levels are not met.
Example: 99.9% uptime, else refund.
------------------------------------------------------
